aa(lp25
VSo, to begin with,
p26
aVwe need to understand what a black hole is
p27
aVso we can understand the proof of a black hole.
p28
aVSo, what is a black hole?
p29
aVWell, in many ways a black hole is an incredibly simple object,
p30
aVbecause there are only three characteristics that you can describe:
p31
aVthe mass,
p32
aVthe spin, and the charge.
p33
aVAnd I'm going to only talk about the mass.
p34
aVSo, in that sense, it's a very simple object.
p35
aVBut in another sense, it's an incredibly complicated object
p36
aVthat we need relatively exotic physics to describe,
p37
aVand in some sense represents the breakdown of our physical understanding
p38
aVof the universe.
